        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 8:14PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 813 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hooks Airport, or near Tomball. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tomball and Hooks Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
